## Anatomy of an If

An `if` statement checks a `bool` condition inside parentheses `()`.
If the condition is `true`, Dart runs the code inside the curly braces `{}`.

```dart
if (score > 100) {
  print('You win!');
}
```
If `score` is 50, nothing happens at all!

## A backup plan

What if the condition is `false` and we DO want something to happen?

We add an `else` block immediately after the closing `}`.

```dart
if (password == '1234') {
  print('Access Granted');
} else {
  print('Access Denied!');
}
```

slides.codeSnippet:
void main() {
  bool isRaining = true;

  if (isRaining) {
    print('Take an umbrella!');
  } else {
    print('Wear sunglasses!');
  }
}

